main event: A civilian reported a sighting of a dark gray saucer-like object with flashing lights in Calumet City, Illinois, observed for 5 minutes on August 15, 1965.
interesting points: The object was observed moving in zig-zags at high speed, too fast for aircraft,The object was much brighter than stars in the sky, yet too slow to be a missile or rocket,The object disappeared beyond trees after the observation,The witness described the lights on the object as one yellow and one green,The observer noted clear weather conditions during the sighting.
sighted object: dark gray saucer-like object with flashing lights
